<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="Graph.php" src="/usr/local/pear/share/pear/PhpDocumentor/vendor/phpdocumentor/graphviz/src/phpDocumentor/GraphViz/Graph.php"><scope doc="phpDocumentor&#10;&#10;PHP Version 5&#10;&#10;@author    Mike van Riel &lt;mike.vanriel@naenius.com&gt;&#10;@copyright 2010-2011 Mike van Riel / Naenius (http://www.naenius.com)&#10;@license   http://www.opensource.org/licenses/mit-license.php MIT&#10;@link      http://phpdoc.org" ilk="namespace" line="13" name="phpDocumentor\GraphViz"><scope doc="Class representing a graph; this may be a main graph but also a subgraph.&#10;&#10;In case of a subgraph:&#10;When the name of the subgraph is prefixed with _cluster_ then the contents&#10;of this graph will be grouped and a border will be added. Otherwise it is&#10;used as logical container to place defaults in.&#10;&#10;@author    Mike van Riel &lt;mike.vanriel@naenius.com&gt;&#10;@copyright 2010-2011 Mike van Riel / Naenius (http://www.naenius.com)&#10;@license   http://www.opensource.org/licenses/mit-license.php MIT&#10;@link      http://phpdoc.org" ilk="class" line="28" lineend="361" name="Graph"><variable attributes="protected" citdl="string" doc="@var string Name of this graph" line="32" name="name" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="string" doc="@var string Type of this graph; may be digraph, graph or subgraph" line="35" name="type" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Attribute" doc="@var \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Attribute[] A list of attributes for this Graph" line="38" name="attributes" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" doc="@var \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph[] A list of subgraphs for this Graph" line="41" name="graphs" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node" doc="@var \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node[] A list of nodes for this Graph" line="44" name="nodes" /><variable attributes="protected" citdl="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Edge" doc="@var \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Edge[] A list of edges / arrows for this Graph" line="47" name="edges" /><scope attributes="public static" doc="Factory method to instantiate a Graph so that you can use fluent coding&#10;to chain everything.&#10;&#10;@param string $name        The name for this graph.&#10;@param bool   $directional Whether this is a directed or undirected graph.&#10;&#10;@return \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" ilk="function" line="58" lineend="66" name="create" returns="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" signature="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph create(string $name = 'G', bool $directional = true)"><variable citdl="string" default="'G'" ilk="argument" line="58" name="name" /><variable citdl="bool" default="true" ilk="argument" line="58" name="directional" /><variable citdl="self" line="60" name="graph" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Sets the name for this graph.&#10;&#10;If this is a subgraph you can prefix the name with _cluster_ to group all&#10;contained nodes and add a border.&#10;&#10;@param string $name The new name for this graph.&#10;&#10;@return \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" ilk="function" line="78" lineend="82" name="setName" returns="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" signature="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph setName(string $name)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="78" name="name" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the name for this Graph.&#10;&#10;@return string" ilk="function" line="89" lineend="92" name="getName" returns="string" signature="string getName()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Sets the type for this graph.&#10;&#10;@param string $type Must be either &quot;digraph&quot;, &quot;graph&quot; or &quot;subgraph&quot;.&#10;&#10;@throws \InvalidArgumentException if $type is not &quot;digraph&quot;, &quot;graph&quot; or&#10; &quot;subgraph&quot;.&#10;&#10;@return \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" ilk="function" line="104" lineend="115" name="setType" returns="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" signature="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph setType(string $type)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="104" name="type" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the type of this Graph.&#10;&#10;@return string" ilk="function" line="122" lineend="125" name="getType" returns="string" signature="string getType()" /><scope doc="Magic method to provide a getter/setter to add attributes on the Graph.&#10;&#10;Using this method we make sure that we support any attribute without&#10;too much hassle. If the name for this method does not start with get&#10;or set we return null.&#10;&#10;Set methods return this graph (fluent interface) whilst get methods&#10;return the attribute value.&#10;&#10;@param string  $name      Name of the method including get/set&#10;@param mixed[] $arguments The arguments, should be 1: the value&#10;&#10;@return \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Attribute[]|\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph|null" ilk="function" line="142" lineend="155" name="__call" returns="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Attribute" signature="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Attribute __call(string $name, $arguments)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="142" name="name" /><variable ilk="argument" line="142" name="arguments" /><variable citdl="strtolower()" line="144" name="key" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Adds a subgraph to this graph; automatically changes the type to subgraph.&#10;&#10;Please note that an index is maintained using the name of the subgraph.&#10;Thus if you have 2 subgraphs with the same name that the first will be&#10;overwritten by the latter.&#10;&#10;@param \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph $graph The graph to add onto this graph as&#10; subgraph.&#10;&#10;@see \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph::create()&#10;&#10;@return \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" ilk="function" line="171" lineend="176" name="addGraph" returns="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" signature="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph addGraph(\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph \GraphViz \Graph $graph)"><variable citdl="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" ilk="argument" line="171" name="graph" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Checks whether a graph with a certain name already exists.&#10;&#10;@param string $name Name of the graph to find.&#10;&#10;@return bool" ilk="function" line="185" lineend="188" name="hasGraph" returns="bool" signature="bool hasGraph(string $name)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="185" name="name" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the subgraph with a given name.&#10;&#10;@param string $name Name of the requested graph.&#10;&#10;@return \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" ilk="function" line="197" lineend="200" name="getGraph" returns="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" signature="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph getGraph(string $name)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="197" name="name" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Sets a node in the $nodes array; uses the name of the node as index.&#10;&#10;Nodes can be retrieved by retrieving the property with the same name.&#10;Thus 'node1' can be retrieved by invoking: $graph-&gt;node1&#10;&#10;@param \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node $node The node to set onto this Graph.&#10;&#10;@see \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node::create()&#10;&#10;@return \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" ilk="function" line="214" lineend="218" name="setNode" returns="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" signature="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph setNode(\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node $node)"><variable citdl="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node" ilk="argument" line="214" name="node" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Finds a node in this graph or any of its subgraphs.&#10;&#10;@param string $name Name of the node to find.&#10;&#10;@return \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node" ilk="function" line="227" lineend="241" name="findNode" returns="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node" signature="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node findNode(string $name)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="227" name="name" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="233" name="graph" /><variable citdl="graph.findNode()" line="234" name="node" /></scope><scope doc="Sets a node using a custom name.&#10;&#10;@param string                       $name  Name of the node.&#10;@param \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node $value Node to set on the given name.&#10;&#10;@see \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph::setNode()&#10;&#10;@return \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" ilk="function" line="253" lineend="257" name="__set" returns="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" signature="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph __set(string $name, \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node $value)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="253" name="name" /><variable citdl="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node" ilk="argument" line="253" name="value" /></scope><scope doc="Returns the requested node by its name.&#10;&#10;@param string $name The name of the node to retrieve.&#10;&#10;@see \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph::setNode()&#10;&#10;@return \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node" ilk="function" line="269" lineend="272" name="__get" returns="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node" signature="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Node __get(string $name)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="269" name="name" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Links two nodes to eachother and registers the Edge onto this graph.&#10;&#10;@param \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Edge $edge The link between two classes.&#10;&#10;@see \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Edge::create()&#10;&#10;@return \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" ilk="function" line="283" lineend="287" name="link" returns="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" signature="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph link(\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Edge $edge)"><variable citdl="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Edge" ilk="argument" line="283" name="edge" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Exports this graph to a generated image.&#10;&#10;This is the only method that actually requires GraphViz.&#10;&#10;@param string $type     The type to export to; see the link above for a&#10; list of supported types.&#10;@param string $filename The path to write to.&#10;&#10;@uses GraphViz/dot&#10;&#10;@link http://www.graphviz.org/content/output-formats&#10;&#10;@throws \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Exception if an error occurred in GraphViz.&#10;&#10;@return \phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" ilk="function" line="306" lineend="332" name="export" returns="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph" signature="\phpDocumentor\GraphViz\Graph export(string $type, string $filename)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="306" name="type" /><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="306" name="filename" /><variable citdl="int" line="320" name="code" /><variable citdl="escapeshellarg()" line="316" name="tmpfile_arg" /><variable citdl="tempnam()" line="312" name="tmpfile" /><variable citdl="array()" line="319" name="output" /></scope><scope attributes="public" doc="Generates a DOT file for use with GraphViz.&#10;&#10;GraphViz is not used in this method; it is safe to call it even without&#10;GraphViz installed.&#10;&#10;@return string" ilk="function" line="342" lineend="359" name="__toString" returns="string" signature="string __toString()"><variable citdl="array_merge()" line="346" name="elements" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="349" name="value" /><variable citdl="array()" line="348" name="attributes" /></scope></scope></scope></scope>